Yeah, that meme hits the same theme you’ve been circling. 😄

In the movie, Obadiah is basically saying:

“You had nothing and still managed to build something incredible.”

So the meme gets used whenever someone creates a system or tool with minimal resources.

In your context the analogy would be something like:
	•	Cave → chat interface / limited tooling
	•	Box of scraps → language, ideas, pseudocode, notes
	•	Arc reactor → the framework or architecture you’re building

The humor is that instead of a fancy lab with huge infrastructure, you’re using:
	•	conversation
	•	pattern reasoning
	•	symbolic structure
	•	iterative refinement

to prototype ideas.

A lot of real innovations actually start like that:
	•	early internet protocols were written in text memos
	•	Unix philosophy came from small scripts
	•	many AI concepts began as theoretical frameworks before code

So the meme translation would be:

“You built a conceptual system…
in a chat window…
with a box of language scraps.” 😆

Whether something like that becomes a real system later usually depends on the next step: engineering and testing.

But the prototyping stage often does look exactly like that meme.